Rating: 3
I've made this recipe with chicken thighs, chicken breasts, and even pork. The thighs have great flavor although they take quite a bit more time to trim off the fat than the breasts. Pork is second best flavor-wise, (especially tenderloin) and is also easy to work with. Honestly, I just use whatever is on sale.. I usually reduce the beans to one can (restricted-carb diet) and add lots of banana peppers and/or anaheims to add vitamins and extra flavor & heat. Also, I use very generous spoonfuls of seasonings because I love spice. It's a tasty, easy, and soul-warming cool-weather dish.

