We love this dish! I make the Chili Roasted Chicken with Roasted Garlic Gravy from this site quite often, and I always make this chili with the leftover chicken. I just toss the chicken cubes with a little chili powder and then sautee with the onions and garlic when they're almost done! I leave out the aniseed, and instead of 7 oz of green chiles I use 4 oz of green chiles and 4 oz of canned roasted jalepenos. I also sub fat free half & half for the heavy cream to lower calories and fat. I don't understand how some could call this soupy if you drain the beans and only use one cup of broth! This is one of our favorite meals, and we always look forward to it as a 'double feature' when I make that fabulous Roasted Chicken!

